import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean().total_seconds()/60))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='distance', data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["distance"].mean():0.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['route'] = data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination']
    route_counts = data.groupby('route').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    route_counts = route_counts.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False).head(10)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='route', y='counts', data=route_counts, palette='Blues_d')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    ax.set_xlabel('Route')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    for i, v in enumerate(route_counts['counts']):
        ax.text(i, v + 1000, str(v), color='black', ha='center')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    data = data.groupby('date').sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of flight counts over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
